sourceMeaningMnemonic: The <radical>mole</radical> has a <radical>knife</radical> ready for your <kanji>arrival</kanji>. You get out of your airplane, you step on the ground and... ouch! You stepped right on the knife, and there's the mole, sticking it out of the ground. "I checked the schedule for your arrival!" it squeaks happily, and disappears.
meaningInfo: Welp, your arrival didn't go smoothly. You have a knife in your foot. I'm not sure what you did to make that mole hate you, but you'll have to be more careful next time.
readingMnemonic: Your <kanji>arrival</kanji> to <ja><reading>とう</reading>きょう</ja> is now ruined. And your next stop is now going to be an arrival at a <ja>とうきょう</ja> hospital to get this mole knife out.
readingInfo: This certainly wasn't the type of arrival you were expecting when you bought your tickets to <ja>とうきょう</ja>.
